<h3>Frame Setup</h3>
<%= md("
The SageFrame component is set up to mirror configurations found in the auto layout feature of Figma,
which is commonly used to create compound layouts.
Here is a summary of the properties and pairings this component makes available:
") %>

<h3>Frame Presets</h3>
<%= md("
Frames have a high level of customization.
The following presets allow for some options to implement common patterns quickly.
Note that presets that do not have border setting are shown here with a background color added
in order to better demonstrate their size and padding.
") %>

<h4>Default</h4>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { background: "grey-200" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<hr />

<%= md("
#### `block`

The basic `block` preset stacks elements vertically with no padding or gap but fills the space available.
Set a specific `width` value to control its width more specifically.
") %>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "block", background: "grey-200" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<hr />

<%= md("
#### `block-hug`

Similar to `block`, the `block-hug` preset stacks elements vertically with no padding or gap.
However, `block-hug` will only take up the space its contents require.
") %>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "block-hug", background: "grey-200" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<hr />

<%= md("
#### `card-sm`

The `card-sm` generates a bordered frame with a small padding and gap setting and a minimal border radius.
") %>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "card-sm" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<hr />

<%= md("
#### `card` and `card-md`

The `card` or `card-md` generates a bordered frame with standard card spacing, gap, and border radius.
") %>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "card" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<hr />

<%= md("
#### `card-lg`

The `card-lg` generates a bordered frame with a generous padding and gap setting and a larger border radius.
") %>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "card-lg" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<hr />

<%= md("
#### `row`

Perfect for laying out most side-by-side content, the `row` places elements horizontally with no border treatment or padding but a standard gap.
") %>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "row", background: "grey-200" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<hr />

<%= md("
#### `row-spread`

Similar to `row`, the `row` places elements horizontally with no border treatment or padding but a standard gap.
In additional, elements are set to spread out evenly within the space available.
") %>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "row-spread", background: "grey-200" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<hr />

<%= md("
#### `row-hug`

Similar to `row`, the `row` places elements horizontally with no border treatment or padding but a standard gap.
However, this preset will only occupy the space its contents require.
") %>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "row-hug", background: "grey-200" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<hr />

<%= md("
#### `stack`

The `stack` preset places elements vertically with no border or padding but a small gap between elements.
") %>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "stack", background: "grey-200" } do %>
  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectitor</p>
  <%= sage_component SageButton, { style: "primary", value: "Learn more" } %>
<% end %>

<h3>Frames in Context</h3>
<%= md("
The true power of SageFrame comes with using it in combination to create compound layouts.
Designed to mimic what developers find in Figma with Auto layout is employed,
a wide range of patterns can be created.
Here are a few samples of what is possible.
") %>

<h4>A custom block</h4>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, {
  preset: "card-lg",
  background: "#fae2d4",
  border: "none",
} do %>
  <%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "stack" } do %>
    <h3>Learn more about products</h3>
    <p>
      Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.
      Etiam faucibus massa vel sem ullamcorper tincidunt.
      Vestibulum pulvinar placerat elit, et rutrum ipsum elementum ac.
    </p>
  <% end %>
  <%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "row-spread" } do %>
    <%= sage_component SageButton, {
      value: "Do it!",
      style: "primary",
    } %>
    <%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "row-hug" } do %>
      <%= sage_component SageButton, {
        value: "Cancel",
        style: "secondary",
        subtle: true,
      } %>
      <%= sage_component SageButton, {
        value: "Options",
        style: "secondary",
        raised: false,
      } %>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>

<h4>A "stat box"</h3>
<%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "card", width: "357px" } do %>
  <%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "row", align: "top-spread" } do %>
    <%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "stack", width: "flex" } do %>
      <%= sage_component SageFrame, { preset: "block" } do %>
        <h3 class="<%= "#{SageClassnames::TYPE::BODY_SMALL} #{SageClassnames::TYPE_COLORS::CHARCOAL_200}" %>">
          All payments
        </h3>
        <%= sage_component SageFrame, {
          direction: "horizontal",
          align: "baseline-left",
          gap: "xs",
          tag: "p"
        } do %>
          <b class="<%= "#{SageClassnames::TYPE::HEADING_5}" %>">
            40
          </b>
          <span class="<%= "#{SageClassnames::TYPE::BODY_XSMALL} #{SageClassnames::TYPE_COLORS::CHARCOAL_100}" %>">
            successfull paymemtns
          </span>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>
      <%= sage_component SageButton, {
        value: "View all",
        icon: { style: "right", name: "arrow-right" },
        style: "primary",
        subtle: true,
      } %>
    <% end %>
    <%= sage_component SageFrame, {
      gap: "xs",
      direction: "vertical",
      align: "top-right",
      width: "120px"
    } do %>
      <%= sage_component SageLabel, {
        color: "published",
        value: "33%",
        icon: "up-small",
      } %>
      <div>
        [chart]
      </div>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
